<T> T
findOneBySearch(Class<T> type, Search search)
          Convenience method for getting a single item
Find a single object of the type associated with this DAO based on matching the supplied search and return it
This search must result in a single item or no items, if there is more than one item then the first item is returned, it is a good idea to sort the search to ensure consistency in case more than one item is found Example usage:
(Sample object of MyClass with "title" property) String title = "this title";
MyItem item = findBySearch(MyItem.class, new Search("title", title);

item will be null if nothing matches "this title", item will be a persistent object if one or more items has the title "this title"

public <T> List<T> findBySearch(Class<T> type,

Description copied from interface: BySearchFinder
Find all objects of the type associated with this DAO based on matching the supplied search and return them in a List

Example usage:
(Sample object of MyClass with "title" property)

String title = "this title";
List l = findBySearch(MyItem.class, new Search("title", title);

The list (l) will contain all objects which have a title which matches "this title"

findOneBySearch

public <T> T findOneBySearch(Class<T> type,
                             Search search)
Description copied from interface: BySearchFinder
Convenience method for getting a single item
Find a single object of the type associated with this DAO based on matching the supplied search and return it
This search must result in a single item or no items, if there is more than one item then the first item is returned, it is a good idea to sort the search to ensure consistency in case more than one item is found

Example usage:
(Sample object of MyClass with "title" property)

String title = "this title";
MyItem item = findBySearch(MyItem.class, new Search("title", title);

item will be null if nothing matches "this title", item will be a persistent object if one or more items has the title "this title"

Specified by:
findOneBySearch in interface BySearchFinder
Parameters:
type - class type of the persistent object
search - the Search object which defines Restriction on data and Order of returned results
Returns:
a persistent object OR null if none are found
See Also:
BySearchFinder.findBySearch(Class, Search)

findByProperties

public List findByProperties(Class entityClass,
                             String[] objectProperties,
                             Object[] values,
                             int[] comparisons,
                             String[] sortProperties)
Deprecated. 

Description copied from interface: ByPropsFinder
Find all objects of the type associated with this DAO based on supplied comparisons and the properties and return them in a List

This adds the ability to sort the returned results be providing the names of the properties you want sorted and the sort order in a string (default sort order is ascending)

String title = "%title";
List l = findByProperties(MyClass.class, new String[] {"title"}, new Object[] {title}, new int[] {ByPropsFinder.LIKE}, new String[] {"title"+ByPropsFinder.DESC});

The list will contain all objects which have a title which ends with "title" sorted by title in descending order

Specified by:
findByProperties in interface ByPropsFinder
Parameters:
entityClass - class type of the persistent object
objectProperties - the names of the properties of the object
values - the values of the properties (can be an array of items)
comparisons - the comparison to make between the property and the value, use the defined constants: e.g. EQUALS, LIKE, etc...
sortProperties - the names of the properties of the object followed by a sort order (default is ascending), use the defined constants: e.g. ASC, DESC
Returns:
a List of 0 or more persistent objects

findByProperties

public List findByProperties(Class entityClass,
                             String[] objectProperties,
                             Object[] values,
                             int[] comparisons,
                             int firstResult,
                             int maxResults)
Deprecated. 

Description copied from interface: ByPropsFinder
Find all objects of the type associated with this DAO based on supplied comparisons and the properties and return them in a List

Comparisons may be used, see the constants for ByPropsFinder
Note: For the LIKE comparison you will need to specify "%" as a wildcard for string comparisons

Example usage:
(Sample object of MyClass with "title" property)

String title = "%title";
List l = findByProperties(MyClass.class, new String[] {"title"}, new Object[] {title}, new int[] {ByPropsFinder.LIKE}, 0, 2);

The list will contain the first 2 objects (if that many exist) which have a title which ends with "title"

Other examples: List l = findByProperties(MyClass.class, new String[] {"title"}, new Object[] {title}, new int[] {ByPropsFinder.LIKE}, 5, 5);
(returns 5 objects starting with the 6th object that has a title ending with "title"
List l = findByProperties(MyClass.class, new String[] {"title"}, new Object[] {title}, new int[] {ByPropsFinder.LIKE}, 10, 0);
(returns all objects starting with the 11th object that has a title ending with "title"

Specified by:
findByProperties in interface ByPropsFinder
Parameters:
entityClass - class type of the persistent object
objectProperties - the names of the properties of the object
values - the values of the properties (can be an array of items)
comparisons - the comparison to make between the property and the value, use the defined constants: e.g. EQUALS, LIKE, etc...
firstResult - the index of the first result object to be retrieved (numbered from 0)
maxResults - the maximum number of result objects to retrieve (or <=0 for no limit)
Returns:
a List of 0 or more persistent objects
